Defendant Thomas S. Zollicoffer in court with attorney Gregg H. Novack.  Defendant Thomas S. Zollicoffer in custody.  Kristin M. Schrank appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, and defendant. 
 
AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  4 1/2 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE to each other and any other time being served, with credit for 99 days served on Count 1.  The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 1/2 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 2 YEARS.

The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program AFTER SERVING THE FIRST 3 YEARS OF THESE SENTENCES.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Referral to Mental health division for mental assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment if necessary;
*Take any medication prescribed only in the manner/dosage as prescribed by a treating physician;
*Obtain AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment if appropriate;
*Cooperate with random urine screens;
*No drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*Defendant prohibited from owning any animals for 5 years;
*Obtain/maintain employment and work hours to the extent allowed by social security- if not receiving social security maintain full-time employment or full time school with part-time employment ;
*Obtain GED or HSED;
*Participate in Cognitive Thinking program;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all mandatory applicable surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs; 

State in compliance with victim rights legislation.  Defense not in agreement with requested restitution; hearing to be held.   The Court ordered that all financial obligations be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.  State's motion to seal the state sentencing memo granted by the court.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  Appeal rights given.
